[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wales' first BOS origami convention comes to Swansea Uni

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An origami convention held by the British Origami Society has come to Wales for the first time.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Hosted at Swansea University's Singleton campus, the "Croeso i Gymru" event invites people to create or display any Wales-themed origami.
Volunteers will hold classes for everyone from beginners to veteran folders.
Artist Maria Sinayskaya, an origami specialist inspired by her mathematics background, will appear.
Visitors are invited to bring along any unfinished models and put them into a box for others to take home.
